{{Otheruses|subject=|other=古代城市Urim|烏爾}}

'''烏陵與土明''' ([[希伯來語|希伯來語]]：'''אוּרִים וְתּוּמִים'''（''Urim vəTummim''）[[英語|英語]]：''Urim and Thummim''；[[阿拉伯語|阿拉伯語]]：'''اوريم وتميم''', ''Ūrīm waṮummīm''），原意分別為“光明”和“完全”，引申意義為“啟示和真理”，是古代[[希伯來人|希伯來人]]在遇到問題或難處時，用以顯明上帝旨意的一種[[預言|預言]]媒介。現代的[[耶穌基督後期聖徒教會|耶穌基督後期聖徒教會]]也用它來翻譯古代經書，例如[[摩爾門經|摩爾門經]]。

== 媒介 ==
<!-- “乌陵”原文中含有咒诅的意思,表示否定;“土明”原文中含有完全的意思,表示确定(撒上14:16-42的“掣签”)。 -->
<!-- 由于''乌陵与土明''这个词汇是复数，在多数情形中并不是一种物体，the device or process could be referred to as 

根据[[犹太教|犹太教]]的教导，a small parchment with 上帝圣名, inscribed on it was slipped into an opening under ''乌陵与土明'' on 大祭司的胸牌, which caused 胸牌 to "发光" and thereby "传达信息" from God to [[以色列人|以色列人]]。

有些学者认为"the" 乌陵与土明由两块晶体组成；但大部分学者并不知道其准确的性质。根据[[希伯来圣经|希伯来圣经]]，stones used for "an" ''乌陵与土明'' were kept in [[摩西|摩西]]的哥哥[[亚伦|亚伦]]的胸牌，（在[[摩尔门教|摩尔门教]]中，[[Joseph_Smith,_Jr.|Joseph Smith, Jr.]]的乌陵与土明由组成"两块透明的石头 set in the rim of a [silver] bow fastened to 胸牌" ({{sourcetext|source=Pearl of Great Price|book=History}} of the Church 4:537). 

近来很多学者指出 the plural nature of the words to argue that there wasn't "a" certain device, but rather 乌陵与土明 was the process or procedure 祭司 used in the casting of lots and some sort of stones or jewels would be the medium。还有人指出在希伯来文中"乌陵与土明"这个词汇，begin with the first letter (''[[aleph|aleph]]'', א) and the final letter (''tav'', ת) of the [[Hebrew_alphabet|Hebrew alphabet]], respectively, and have suggested that the device contained these and perhaps other letters of the Hebrew alphabet, which were used as [[lottery|lots]] to determine the response of the [[oracle|oracle]].  

There is some evidence that ''乌陵与土明'' were/was used as a [[lot|lot]] that provided "yes" or "no" answers, depending upon whether 乌陵或土明 came into play, as manipulated by a Hebrew [[oracle|oracle]]. There is also evidence that the medium was used as an [[ordeal|ordeal]] to establish a person's guilt or innocence.

The Septuagint text and the Masoretic text differ in the area of I Samuel 14:41. MT separates a casting of lots with using the UT, and the LXX appears to treat both as the same. Note the clear differences in these translations,

"Then Saul said, 'O Lord, God of Israel, why have you not answered your servant this day? If the guilt is in me or in Jonathan my son, O Lord, God of Israel, give Urim; and if you indicate that it is in the people of Israel, give Thummim.' And Jonathan and Saul were taken, but the people escaped." I Sam14:41 (LXX)

"And he said to all Israel, 'You will be to one side, and I and my son Jonathan will be to one side." And the people answered Saul, "Do what is good in your eyes.' And Saul said to the Lord God of Israel, "Give a perfect lot," whereupon Jonathan and Saul were taken, and the people escaped. And Saul said, "Cast lots between me and Jonathan my son;" and Jonathan was taken." {{bibleverse|1|Samuel|14:40-42|JP}} (MT)

It is stated in the Scriptures (concerning this account), that God did not answer Saul by the UT that day (verse 37), so Saul resorted to the casting of lots instead. The casting of lots (see {{bibleverse||Leviticus|16:8|JP}}) should always be viewed as distinct from the function of the UT. While the use of lots can only give a yes or no answer, we find one instance when the UT was consulted where a whole conversation took place. -->
== 在圣经中 ==
[[希伯来圣经|希伯来圣经]]中最早提及''乌陵与土明''是在[[出埃及记|出埃及记]]28章30节，说到大祭司[[亚伦|亚伦]]进到[[耶和华|耶和华]]面前的时候，要常将以色列人的决断的胸牌带在胸前，乌陵和土明就放在决断的胸牌里。许多学者相信''乌陵与土明'' 最初是和其他的宝石一同放在犹太大祭司圣衣前的胸牌里
<!--  when he officiated in the tabernacle or temple. Upon the death of 亚伦和摩西，约书亚 was instructed to present himself to the high priest for the counsel of 乌陵与土明 when he wished to consult God. This was in contrast to 摩西，who was believed to speak to God directly, and indicated that Joshua would not normally receive direct revelation. The last agreed-upon reference to 乌陵与土明 in 在圣经[[以斯拉记|以斯拉记]]和[[尼希米记|尼希米记]] when, as [[耶路撒冷圣殿|耶路撒冷圣殿]] and its worship practices are being restored, those who cannot prove their lineage as [[祭司|祭司]]们 are commanded to wait for a priest who was worthy to use 乌陵与土明 to confirm their eligibility.  This seems to indicate that 乌陵与土明 were present, but that there was no one left at the time with sufficient authority to use them. -->
=== 基督教观点 ===
有人认为''乌陵与土明'' 就是[[拈阄|拈阄]]的另一个名称，或是[[抽籤|抽籤]]
<!-- rather than a device that is used as a medium. Because of this context, some 传统 {{fact}}认为在[[使徒行传|使徒行传]]中拣选马提亚代替[[加略人犹大|加略人犹大]]the casting of lot 就是用乌陵与土明来拈阄 rather than by "the" 乌陵与土明。In either case,乌陵与土明is not mentioned specifically in Biblical text in regard to this calling. -->

== 非圣经参考 ==

=== 耶穌基督後期聖徒教會 ===
乌陵与土明在[[耶穌基督後期聖徒教會|耶穌基督後期聖徒教會]]中扮演重要的角色。[[约瑟·斯密|约瑟·斯密]]曾使用过它们，根据它们翻译了[[耶穌基督後期聖徒教會|耶穌基督後期聖徒教會]]。传说斯密还通过它们得到了神圣的启示，写成了《[[教义和圣约|教义和圣约]]》和[[圣经约瑟·斯密译本|圣经约瑟·斯密译本]]的一部分。许多约瑟·斯密身边的人见过乌陵与土明；但此外只有奥立弗·考得利一个人尝试使用它们得到过启示（{{sourcetext|source=教义和圣约|book=Section 9}}）. 

马丁·哈里斯根据查尔斯·安森的回忆，认为乌陵与土明是一副巨大的黄金眼镜，每个镜头可以用用两只眼睛来看。[https://web.archive.org/web/20061213225146/http://thedigitalvoice.com/enigma/essays/AAffair1.htm "安森事件"]

[https://web.archive.org/web/20081010162856/http://scriptures.lds.org/bdu/urmndthm LDS 圣经辞典]将''乌陵与土明''定义为"一种上帝预备的工具，帮助人们从上帝得到启示并翻译成语言。" 在摩尔门经中先知the Brother of Jared和Mosiah都使用名为"解释者"的设备为人们得到启示。[http://scriptures.lds.org/dc/17/1#1 教义和圣约] {{Wayback|url=http://scriptures.lds.org/dc/17/1#1 |date=20100519065827 }}阐明解释者确实是根据乌陵与土明。摩尔门教中乌陵与土明由[[先知|先知]]使用，尽管耶穌基督後期聖徒教會承认任何一个有预言的恩赐者都能不时预卜未来。

=== 共济会 ===
<!-- [[共济会|共济会]]传说 (taught during the 13, 14 and 21 degrees ceremonies of Masonry)和 Kabbalistic 传统认为乌陵与土明 是 part of the recovered artifacts taken from 所罗门圣殿 after [[Hiram_Abif|Hiram Abif]]在保护圣殿宝库时被杀。根据这个传说，乌陵与土明 and other recovered 财宝 were placed back in 圣殿宝库中。 -->

=== 通俗文化 ===
在通俗文学中，寻宝人寻找乌陵与土明构成了约翰·贝莱尔的小说《巫师幽灵的复仇》的中心情节，显然故意亵渎了[[亞瑟·柯南·道爾|亞瑟·柯南·道爾]]的短篇小说《犹太胸牌》。

在比尔·梅耶的基督教小说《上帝的面孔》中，丹尼尔·劳森牧师为了听见上帝的声音，和恐怖分子易卜拉欣·马吉德竞相发现旧约中提及的乌陵与土明，和大祭司的胸牌上的12块宝石。

有人认为，对乌陵与土明的描述证实了[[古代太空人|古代太空人]]。

在保罗·克尔霍的小说''[[炼金术士_(小说)|煉金术士]]''（《牧羊少年奇幻之旅》）中，一位老人自称是撒冷国王，给主角圣地亚哥“小男孩”两块石头，一块白色，一块黑色，并告诉他这就是乌陵与土明。他继续说这些石头能用来决断，黑色意味“是”而白色意味“否”。这位老人戴着华丽的金色胸牌，石头在在给圣地亚哥之前已经睡眠。
<!-- 在电影''The Dark Crystal''中，a [[Healer|Healer]] from the mystic urRu race is named urIm, probably after 乌陵与土明。In addition to the name, urIm references esoteric devices by using [[acupuncture|acupuncture]], baths, and [[amulets|amulets]] to restore balance to his fellow [[urRu|urRu]], and by making patterns in [[空气|空气]]和[[水|水]] with his many hands to reduce and restore the "fires of the soul". -->

